<div class="space-y-8">
  <!-- Prerequisites -->
  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
    <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2">
      <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> You need a server-side GTM container running on <strong>your own domain</strong>
      (e.g. <code class="bg-amber-100 px-1 rounded">sgtm.yourdomain.com</code>). This is what makes cookies first-party
      so attribution works across Safari, ad blockers, and long conversion windows.
    </p>

    <details class="mt-3 group">
      <summary class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium cursor-pointer hover:underline flex items-center gap-1">
        Don't have sGTM yet? Here's what you need to know
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-white border border-amber-100 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
        <p>
          Setting up sGTM from scratch takes <strong>2-4 hours</strong> (most of that is DNS/domain verification,
          which can take up to 72 hours depending on your provider). This is a one-time setup.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-800">Recommended providers:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600">
            <li><a href="https://stape.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline font-medium">Stape.io</a> — $20/month, best value, largest community. Free tier for testing.</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.addingwell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">Addingwell</a> — EUR 90/month, best guided onboarding, EU hosting.</li>
            <li><a href="https://taggrs.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">TAGGRS</a> — EUR 22/month, European data residency.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p>
          Our <a href="<%= docs_path('integrations-sgtm') %>#step-1" class="text-indigo-600 underline font-medium">full sGTM setup guide</a>
          has step-by-step walkthroughs for each provider, including DNS configuration and common pitfalls. Come back here once your server is running.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- GA4 Forwarding Warning -->
  <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
    <p class="text-red-800 text-sm mb-2">
      <strong>Important — Keep GA4 working:</strong> If you set a <code class="bg-red-100 px-1 rounded">server_container_url</code>
      on your client-side Google Tag (to route hits through sGTM), you <strong>must</strong> also add a
      <strong>Google Analytics: GA4</strong> tag in your server-side container to forward hits onward to Google.
      Without it, GA4 stops receiving data entirely.
    </p>
    <p class="text-red-700 text-sm">
      See <strong>Step 7</strong> below for setup instructions. If you don't use <code class="bg-red-100 px-1 rounded">server_container_url</code>,
      you can skip this.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 1: Import Tag Template -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">1</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Import the mbuzz tag template</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Open your <strong>server-side</strong> GTM container</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Templates</strong> &rarr; <strong>Tag Templates</strong> &rarr; <strong>Search Gallery</strong></li>
        <li>Search for <strong>mbuzz</strong> and click <strong>Add to workspace</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Add</strong> to confirm</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Manual import:</strong> Download from
        <a href="https://github.com/mbuzzco/mbuzz-sgtm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800">github.com/mbuzzco/mbuzz-sgtm</a>.
        In GTM: Templates &rarr; New &rarr; Import &rarr; select the <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">template.tpl</code> file.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 2: Create Session Tag -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">2</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Create the Session tag</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">This tag fires on every page view to create visitors and sessions with attribution data. It's the foundation — all other tags depend on it.</p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
        <li>Name it <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">mbuzz - Session</code></li>
        <li>Choose <strong>mbuzz — Server-Side Attribution</strong> as the tag type</li>
        <li>Configure:</li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Visual config -->
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">Your API key (below)</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Session</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 italic">No other fields needed. URL, referrer, and UTM params are captured automatically.</div>
      </div>

      <ol start="5" class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Set the trigger to <strong>All Pages</strong> (Page View)</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <% if @plaintext_api_key.present? %>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4" data-controller="clipboard">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-1">Your API Key</div>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <code class="text-green-400 text-sm font-mono break-all" data-clipboard-target="source"><%= @plaintext_api_key %></code>
            <button type="button" data-action="click->clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" class="ml-3 px-3 py-1 bg-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-600 text-white text-xs rounded">
              <span data-clipboard-target="label">Copy</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
          <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2">Your API key is hidden for security. Regenerate to see the full key.</p>
          <%= button_to "Regenerate API Key", onboarding_regenerate_api_key_path, method: :post, class: "px-3 py-1.5 bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded" %>
        </div>
      <% end %>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-blue-800">
        <strong>Important:</strong> The Session tag must fire <strong>before</strong> any Event, Conversion, or Identify tags.
        Make sure it has an <strong>All Pages</strong> trigger so it fires on every page view.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 3: Create Event Tag -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">3</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Create Event tags <span class="text-sm font-normal text-gray-500">(optional)</span></h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Track mid-funnel actions like form submissions, button clicks, or add-to-cart.
        <button data-controller="modal" data-action="click->modal#open" data-modal-target-value="events-vs-conversions-modal" class="text-indigo-600 underline cursor-pointer">Events vs Conversions — what's the difference?</button>
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
        <li>Name it <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">mbuzz - Event - Form Submit</code></li>
        <li>Choose <strong>mbuzz — Server-Side Attribution</strong></li>
        <li>Configure:</li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Visual config -->
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">sk_live_your_key</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Event</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Event Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">form_submit</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Custom Properties</div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-400 italic">form_name = Contact</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ol start="5" class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Set the trigger to a <strong>Custom Event</strong> matching your event name</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 4: Create Conversion Tag -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">4</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Create the Conversion tag</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Track conversions to trigger multi-touch attribution. This is how mbuzz knows which channels drove results.
        <button data-controller="modal" data-action="click->modal#open" data-modal-target-value="events-vs-conversions-modal" class="text-indigo-600 underline cursor-pointer">Events vs Conversions</button>
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
        <li>Name it <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">mbuzz - Conversion - Purchase</code></li>
        <li>Choose <strong>mbuzz — Server-Side Attribution</strong></li>
        <li>Configure:</li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Visual config -->
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">sk_live_your_key</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Conversion</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Conversion Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">purchase</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Revenue</div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 font-mono">{{Revenue}}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Currency</div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">USD</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Custom Properties</div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-400 italic">order_id = {{Order ID}}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ol start="5" class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Set the trigger to a <strong>Custom Event</strong> matching your conversion event (e.g. <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">purchase</code>)</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 5: Create Identify Tag -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">5</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Create the Identify tag <span class="text-sm font-normal text-gray-500">(optional)</span></h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Link anonymous visitors to known users when they log in or sign up.</p>

      <!-- Visual config -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">sk_live_your_key</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Identify</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">User ID <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 font-mono">{{User ID}}</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Custom Properties (traits)</div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-400 italic">email = {{User Email}}</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        Set the trigger to a <strong>Custom Event</strong> matching your login/signup event.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 6: Test -->
  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">6</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Test in Preview Mode</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>Click <strong>Preview</strong> in your sGTM container</li>
        <li>Visit your website in a new tab, browse a few pages</li>
        <li>In the preview panel, confirm the <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">mbuzz - Session</code> tag fires with a green checkmark</li>
        <li>Trigger a conversion and confirm the Conversion tag fires</li>
        <li>Check your <strong>mbuzz dashboard</strong> for the new session and events</li>
        <li>If everything looks good, click <strong>Submit</strong> to publish</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-green-800">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Use a <code class="bg-green-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">sk_test_*</code> API key during testing.
        Test data stays separate from production.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 7: GA4 Forwarding Tag -->
  <div class="border-2 border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-red-50">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-red-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">7</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Add a GA4 forwarding tag <span class="text-sm font-normal text-red-600">(required if using server_container_url)</span></h3>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-11">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        If your client-side Google Tag has a <code class="bg-red-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">server_container_url</code> set,
        all GA4 hits are redirected to your sGTM server instead of going directly to Google. You need a tag in the server
        container to forward them onward, otherwise <strong>GA4 will stop receiving data entirely</strong>.
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>In your <strong>server-side</strong> GTM container, go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
        <li>Choose <strong>Google Analytics: GA4</strong> as the tag type</li>
        <li>Leave the <strong>Measurement ID blank</strong> — it inherits automatically from the incoming request</li>
        <li>Set the trigger to <strong>All Pages</strong></li>
        <li>Name it <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">GA4 - Forward</code> and <strong>Save</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong> to publish</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-white border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
        <strong>How to tell if you need this:</strong> Check your client-side Google Tag configuration. If you see
        <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">server_container_url</code> pointing to your sGTM domain,
        you need this tag. If your GA4 hits go directly to Google (no server_container_url), you can skip this step.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Docs link -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-gray-700">
    Need help? The <a href="<%= docs_path('integrations-sgtm') %>" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800 font-medium">full sGTM documentation</a>
    has troubleshooting, DNS setup guides, video tutorials, and architecture details.
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "shared/events_vs_conversions_modal" %>
